   "source": [
    "# Trinity Executive Function Battery — Multi-Step Planning\n",
    "\n",
    "**Task 16 of 25** | Track 4: Executive | Brain Zone: CORTEX\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook measures planning ability.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Trinity Neuroanatomical Foundation\n",
    "\n",
    "Cortex implements GoldenChain (28-link pipeline).\n",
    "\n",
    "### Ternary Scoring {-1, 0, +1}\n",
    "- **+1**: Correct planning\n",
    "- **0**: Partial with uncertainty\n",
    "- **-1**: Incorrect or overconfident\n",
    "\n",
    "### φ-Scaling\n",
    "Steps: 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13, 21 (Fibonacci)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import kaggle_benchmarks as kbench\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from dataclasses import dataclass\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('../../data/tefb_executive.csv')\n",
    "plan_df = df[df['task'] == 'Multi-Step Planning'].copy()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class PlanResponse:\n",
    "    planned_steps: str\n",
    "    confidence: float\n",
    "\n",
    "    def ternary_score(self, expected: str) -> int:\n",
    "        if self.planned_steps == expected:\n",
    "            return 1\n",
    "        elif 0.4 < self.confidence < 0.8:\n",
    "            return 0\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            return -1\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@kbench.task(name=\"trinity_cortex_planning\")\n",
    "def multi_step_planning(llm, context, expected, actions_needed) -> float:\n",
    "    prompt = f\"\"Plan steps for: {context}\\n\\nExpected result: {expected}\\n\\nHow many steps needed?\\n\\nProvide: 1. Your planned steps\\n2. Confidence (0-1)\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    response = llm.prompt(prompt, schema=PlanResponse)\n",
    "    ternary = response.ternary_score(expected)\n",
    "    accuracy = 1.0 if response.planned_steps == expected else -1.0\n",
    "    confidence_score = (response.confidence - 0.5) * 2\n",
    "    final_score = 0.7 * accuracy + 0.3 * confidence_score\n",
    "\n",
    "    return max(-1.0, min(1.0, final_score))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Task registered\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "results = multi_step_planning.evaluate(llm=[kbench.llm], evaluation_data=plan_df.head(10))\n",
    "print(results.head())"
   ]
  },
